metadata.name: Prometheus's Gift
metadata.description:
The mighty titan believed in those humans born from the dust. 
He believed we can be more than just a parody of the gods, dumb and lost.
He stole the fire from the Olympians, the sparkle of civilization, and he gave it to us. 
As a punishment for this sacrilege, he was chained to a rock for eternity by Zeus itself, while eagles ate him alive.
